from Deciphers Web-Site:

    Warren Holland, Chairman & CEO Of Decipher
    Announces Great Star Trek Customizable Card
    Game News

    ------------
    Warren Holland
    Chairman and CEO
    ------------

    Since our groundbreaking license with
    Paramount the end of November, we have been
    very busy behind the scenes planning the
    entire Star Trek[TM] Customizable Card
    Game[TM] line for the next four years. I
    realize we have released very little news
    mostly because the expanded license brought
    so many new dynamics to our plans. There is
    so much work going on at once, that our
    schedules are changing almost daily. Have
    no fear... Star Trek is getting a
    tremendous amount of attention at Decipher.

    Decipher and Paramount have been working
    together, diligently gathering new
    resources for First Contact[TM], Deep Space
    Nine[TM], Voyager[TM] and The Next
    Generation[TM]. An enormous amount of work
    is taking place on new cards, distribution,
    marketing, tournaments and other
    enhancements to the game. You are about to
    benefit from the fruits of this labor. ;-)

    I know one product everyone wants to know
    about is The Fajo Collection[TM].
    Sooooooo... I decided it was time I gave
    you a sneak peek at what's in store for
    this revolutionary product. Before I do, I
    thought I would give you an overview of
    what's coming for the Star Trek
    Customizable Card Game as a whole. The
    following represents product for one year
    of our license. As you read, keep in mind
    that under the previous license with
    Paramount, only one expansion set a year
    was introduced. ;-)

    You have already seen the Introductory
    Two-Player Games. In 1997, the flood gates
    will open...

    * The First Anthology - will be released
      in May. This wonderful product is
      packed with value and features, among
      other things, six rare white-border
      "preview cards" from upcoming DS9 and
      Voyager expansions. It also contains a
      $10 coupon off the price of The Fajo
      Collection, plus a very cool Star Trek
      Customizable Card Game 800-card
      storage box.

    * The Fajo Collection - Mid-year we have
      an innovative, limited-edition,
      special expansion set that will be
      sold directly by a new Decipher
      subsidiary. Think of this as The
      Franklin Mint of the collectible card
      game industry. The Fajo Collection is
      designed to "break new ground and blow
      your mind." I will tell you more about
      this exciting product below.

    * First Contact expansion set -In the
      third quarter we will introduce THE
      BORG in an exciting expansion which I
      expect will bring an enormous amount
      of attention to this game.

    * A mystery expansion set -In the fourth
      quarter, we originally planned to
      introduce an expansion set called
      Holodeck Adventures. No longer. We
      have decided instead to push forward
      another expansion that has been in
      development. This as yet unnamed set
      will introduce a totally new gameplay
      mechanism to the Star Trek
      Customizable Card Game... enhanced
      battling! This is the most requested
      gameplay element from players, and
      that's what we're going to deliver.
      Very, very exciting. (Of course,
      playing this system is optional.) Not
      only will battling be more pervasive,
      it will be more exhilarating and
      unpredictable!

    * Deep Space Nine -In late 1997 or early
      1998, we expect to introduce the first
      DS9 product which will provide "a new
      entry point" into our game, yet the
      cards will be 100% compatible with all
      cards in the Star Trek Customizable
      Card Game universe.

    * Uncut sheets - Both limited edition
      black-border and unlimited edition
      white-border unframed, uncut sheets
      will be offered. These items are truly
      works of art. We anticipate a
      three-sheet set of white-border
      Premiere (a common, uncommon and rare)
      will sell for about $100, plus
      shipping and handling. The Fajo
      Collection will include a 50% discount
      coupon making a set of three uncut
      sheets cost far less than many fine
      art posters. That's an amazing value.
      Black-border limited edition uncut
      sheets are designed for very serious
      collectors. The sets will be extremely
      rare... only 500 Premiere black-border
      sets will ever be offered to the
      public worldwide. Expect a high price,
      something on the order of a complete
      black-border set of cards. These
      sheets will be signed, numbered and
      include a certificate of authenticity.
      These unique products are sure to
      spark excitement with die-hard Star
      Trek fans!

    * Foreign language sets - Also at the
      end of 1997 or early 1998, we expect
      to introduce the first foreign
      language versions of Star Trek
      Customizable Card Game.

    There's more! Our Star Trek Customizable
    Card Game tournament structure is nearing
    completion. It will include sanctioned
    tournaments, junior tournaments and
    sanctioned sealed deck tournaments.
    Decipher has developed a proprietary
    software tool exclusively for tournament
    directors to assist them in running
    tournaments efficiently, and to report
    tournament results quickly for a "worldwide
    player ranking system." I'm also happy to
    announce that we are hot at work on Palace,
    our Star Trek Customizable Card Game
    graphic chat area for our web site. We
    introduced this feature for Star Wars
    Customizable Card Game a few months ago to
    resounding applause. I must say, this
    project will arrive a bit earlier that we
    originally expected. Our Star Trek CCG
    Palace is quite impressive and very, very
    cool.

    Whewwwwwww. So, there you have it... an
    overview. That's a lot, don't you think?
    But, I have something else to share with
    you... The Fajo Collection.

    Until his arrest in 2366, Kivas Fajo
    ambitiously collected the greatest
    artifacts in the galaxy-by any means
    possible.

    I am very pleased to announce a special
    Star Trek Customizable Card Game portfolio
    named after this unique character and his
    fanatical pursuit of one-of-a-kind objects.
    Thankfully, you don't have to stoop to
    Kivas' unscrupulous level when acquiring
    the best. Our exclusive collection will be
    printed in a numbered, limited edition of
    40,000 sets, approximately the same as the
    number of ultra-rare Future Enterprise
    cards printed.

    You have never seen anything like The Fajo
    Collection. Think of it as an item you
    would expect from The Franklin Mint or
    Sharper Image... exceptional, valuable and
    innovative. Decipher has crafted eighteen
    super-rare cards containing some of the
    most innovative features and gameplay to
    ever appear in a collectible card game. The
    cards arrive in a presentation binder
    housed in a protective slip cover case
    (like fine books).

    I've heard rumors that The Fajo Collection
    will contain nothing but artifacts...
    that's NOT correct. You will find
    long-anticipated personnel cards as well as
    artifacts, ships and a wide variety of
    other card types. Powerful. Beautiful.
    Highly desirable cards. A number of cards
    are manufactured using unique printing
    techniques and arguably have some of the
    most dynamic art ever to emerge from
    Decipher's design studio.

    I won't reveal all the secrets, but here's
    a sample of the excitement...

    * 1962 Roger Maris Baseball Card - an
      artifact based upon the episode "The
      Most Toys," which featured Kivas Fajo
      himself. Ever since a prototype of
      this card was shown at GenCon, it has
      been rumored that it would appear in
      The Fajo Collection. Okay, okay... I
      confirm that it will. Not only is the
      gameplay of this Artifact
      extraordinary, but the card arrives in
      your hands... with "the original
      bubble gum smell." Too cool! Ohhhhh...
      don't worry, the card will not smell
      like bubble gum when you put it in
      your deck. ;-)

    * DNA Metamorphosis - a planet/space
      dilemma based upon the episode
      "Identity Crisis." In this show,
      Geordi has a five year old dormant
      infection that activates, rewriting
      his DNA and compelling him to return
      to Tarchannen III. There Geordi is
      transformed into an invisible
      reptilian humanoid observable only
      when examined under ultraviolet light.
      Decipher's artists have re-created
      this special effect by printing
      sections of this card with special
      luminous inks. Awesome!

    * Qapla'! - an Interrupt card. Sooooo,
      it's an interrupt card. What's so
      special? Well, actually it's a qaghwI'
      written entirely in the Klingon
      language. Wow... I hear Klingon fans
      going nuts. haha

    We haven't forgotten our Romulan fans
    either (they sometimes feel left out, but I
    believe they get their revenge in this
    set). Two cards in particular will thrill a
    Romulan lover beyond belief. For example,
    can you say, "Mindmeld?" Also, the set
    includes two powerful alternate universe
    ships that are linked in a rather unusual
    way. Actually, every card in this portfolio
    is a treasure. How much of a treasure?
    Well, I've mentioned a few examples, but
    I'll reveal two more (and that's all.
    hahaha)... two of the most sought after
    personnel cards every created... Guinan and
    Locutus of Borg.

    Guinan!

    Locutus of Borg!

    Wow! Yes, the favorite bartender on the
    Enterprise and the Big Borg Man himself
    will appear in this special set. ;-) We
    have no idea what these cards will go for
    on the singles market. What would you pay
    for Guinan? $20? $30? or Locutus of Borg?
    $30? $40? Your guess is as good as ours.

    Each portfolio will contain the same
    eighteen cards (The Fajo Collection is not
    randomized). Every card in The Collection
    has at least one feature you have never
    seen before, and each card breaks new
    ground in terms of gameplay and "cool
    factor." ;-) Also, all eighteen cards are
    tournament playable.

    The Fajo Collection contains a certificate
    of authenticity bearing the signatures of
    key members of Decipher's product
    development and art teams, a collectible
    art poster showcasing the entire Star Trek
    Collectible Card Game universe, a
    Proof-of-Purchase certificate good for up
    to $30 in rebates from purchases of the
    First Anthology (up to three $10 coupons
    can be used), a rules supplement covering
    new gameplay innovations in The Fajo
    Collection cards and a special 50% discount
    offer on the first white-border uncut
    sheets ever sold to the general public from
    the Premiere edition of Star Trek: The Next
    Generation Customizable Card Game. This
    discount offer is valued at $50. Expect The
    Fajo Collection to cost about $80, plus
    shipping and handling.

    The Fajo Collection will be sold directly
    and exclusively by a new Decipher
    subsidiary. Purchases will be limited to 4
    sets per household. Although it is not
    being sold at wholesale, retailers and
    distributors will also be able to purchase
    up to four sets (we expect primarily for
    singles sales). Now... I know... the next
    question is... "When will it ship?" I
    mentioned a projected date earlier in this
    letter, but I'm not prepared to announce an
    official release date as of yet. The
    enormity of our new Star Trek license
    required that we redesign a few cards. For
    example, when First Contact (the movie) was
    released, it had an impact on the icons and
    design of Locutus of Borg.

    Further information on the release date and
    ordering instructions for The Fajo
    Collection will be appearing on Decipher's
    web site at www.decipher.com, and in ads of
    respected industry publications such as
    Scrye and Inquest.

    I'm pleased to have shared some of our
    plans with you. The Star Trek Customizable
    Card Game has a very bright future.
    Decipher views The Fajo Collection as a
    special celebration of this wonderful game.
    Our designers and artists have crafted a
    masterpiece!

    Once again, I welcome you to a universe
    with endless possibilities!

    Warren Holland
    Chairman & CEO
    Decipher Inc.

